  "prompt": "How do I get printouts of past IRCTC journey tickets?",
  "response": "To get printouts of past IRCTC journey tickets, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Visit IRCTC Website:**\n   Open the IRCTC website at www.irctc.co.in.\n\n2. **Login to Your Account:**\n   Log in using your credentials (User ID and Password). If you have forgotten your password, you can use the 'Forgot Password' option.\n\n3. **Go to \u2018My Bookings\u2019:**\n   Once logged in, navigate to the 'My Bookings' section. This may be under the menu options like 'Booked Ticket History'.\n\n4. **Search Your Past Journey:**\n   In the 'Booked Ticket History' or similar section, you will find a list of all your past bookings. You can filter this list based on date and other parameters to find the specific journey ticket you need.\n\n5. **Select the Ticket:**\n   Identify the ticket you want to print. Click on the Ticket Number or the PNR (Passenger Name Record).\n\n6. **Print Ticket:**\n   After clicking, you will be able to view the complete details of the ticket. There should be an option to 'Print Ticket'. Click on it and your past journey ticket will be printed.\n\n7. **Alternative Method - Email:**\n   If you have your journey ticket in your email, you can directly open the corresponding email and print the e-ticket from there.\n\n8. **Mobile App:**\n   If you prefer using the mobile app, open the IRCTC Rail Connect app on your smartphone, log in, go to 'My Bookings', and follow similar steps to view and print the ticket.\n\nEnsure you have a printer connected to your computer or have access to a facility where you can print your ticket. If you face technical difficulties, you can contact IRCTC customer support for assistance.",
